text: Enrique Tornero Hernandez (born May 30, 1980 in Plasencia, CÃ¡ceres) is a swimmer from Spain. He has a disability and is an S9 type swimmer. He raced at the 1996 Summer Paralympics. He finished first in the 400 meter freestyle race. He finished third in the 4 x 100 meter 34 points freestyle relay. He raced at the 2000 Summer Paralympics.
